<div class="project-body">
  {% call section("My Role & Responsibilities") %}
  <ul>
    <li>Planned the reduction end-to-end with the leadership team and in-house employment law counsel — including sensitive individual dimensions such as visa status and compliance considerations</li>
    <li>Partnered directly with the Managing Director to design the future organisation: identifying priorities, defining the roles the new structure needed, and mapping existing talent against it</li>
    <li>Participated in the collective consultation process and personally conducted notification conversations with affected employees</li>
    <li>Led the human side of the aftermath: reassuring top talent of their place in the new organisation and being a consistent, open door for a shaken team</li>
  </ul>
  {% endcall %}

  {% call section("The Challenge") %}
  <p>Before the acquisition, this was a genuinely happy, high-performing organisation — which made the news land even harder. The reduction came as a shock to most (complete confidentiality meant there were no rumours to soften the blow), morale dropped sharply, and uncertainty began driving attrition in a team that had never had an attrition problem.</p>
  <p>The task was twofold: execute a legally complex, multi-country reduction with speed and precision — and then bring a grieving team back to believing in its future.</p>

  {{ pullQuote('"Several colleagues thanked me, emotionally, on their way out — because they felt treated like humans, not headcount."', "The moment that defines how I approach every restructuring") }}
  {% endcall %}

  {% call section("The Solution & Outcome") %}
  {{ phaseStrip([
    { label: "Design", description: "New org built around priorities with the MD — not even cuts" },
    { label: "Consult", description: "Legally rigorous, individually sensitive, fully confidential" },
    { label: "Transition", description: "Every conversation held with dignity and empathy" },
    { label: "Rebuild", description: "Reassurance, open doors, and the slow return of spirit" }
  ]) }}
  <p>We designed the new organisation around clear priorities rather than simply cutting evenly, which meant the smaller team could still fully support the franchise slate — aided by newly found efficiencies and closer collaboration with Xbox. For those who stayed, I invested heavily in one-to-one reassurance, and slowly the spirit returned: engagement held within four points of pre-acquisition levels, attrition stabilised at 7%, and the project was executed with remarkable accuracy and speed.</p>
  <p>What this period taught me: in business-critical moments, a People team that trusts each other completely is not a nice-to-have — it's the thing that makes speed, precision and humanity possible at the same time.</p>
  {% endcall %}
